  "text": "Up to this point, the structures we discussed are mathematically essentially under control (see e.g. [CITATION_1] ). There is, however, one further crucial aspect of conformal blocks, known as factorization. The curveX is allowed to have ordinary double points. Blowing up such a point p yields a new curveX ′ with a projection toX under which p has two pre-images p ′ ± . By factorization one means the existence of a canonical isomorphism",
